# File: app/_data/login.json.ab
# Purpose: Mock authentication API response fixture used for local development or test data
# Dependencies: []

## Overview
A static JSON fixture that simulates a successful login API response. Contains a hardcoded authentication token and a minimal user object. Used as mock/stub data during development when the backend is unavailable, or as a reference for the expected shape of the login API response consumed by the `Auth` service and `appService`.

## Interface
JSON object with two top-level keys:
- `token` (string) — authentication token value; hardcoded as `"asd"` in this fixture
- `user` (object) — authenticated user record containing:
  - `id` (string) — user identifier; hardcoded as `"1"`
  - `person` (object) — nested person data:
    - `name` (string) — display name; hardcoded as `"User 1"`

## Dependencies
No project-level `.ab` dependencies.

## Implementation Notes
- Located in `app/_data/`, which is the Yeoman Angular generator convention for JSON mock data files
- This fixture defines the minimum required shape for the login response; the real API response likely includes additional fields (email, avatar, roles, etc.)
- The `appService` stores user data from this response structure in `$localStorage` after login
- The `Auth` service stores the `token` value in a cookie as `Authorization: Token <token>`
- This file is not loaded by the Angular application at runtime; it serves as reference data or is used by tooling/tests that mock HTTP calls
